com.spazedog.lib.rootfw4

Class Shell.StreamCollector

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spazedog.lib.rootfw4.Shell.StreamCollector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ShellStreamer.StreamListener
    Enclosing class:
    Shell

    public static class Shell.StreamCollector
extends Object
implements ShellStreamer.StreamListener
    This is mostly an internal class that is used to collect data from the ShellStreamer. But since there really is no reason for making this private, it's not. But should this class be extended and parsed to methods in Shell, it might be a good idea to review the source for it first. It is used to make synchronized calls to ShellStreamer that normally works asynchronized.

      • onStreamStart

        public void onStreamStart(ShellStreamer shell)
        Description copied from interface: ShellStreamer.StreamListener
        Called when a new stream has been started (Added from the queue)

        All streams that is started using ShellStreamer.startStream(StreamListener) is put into a queue. This method is called when the stream is pulled from the queue and started. It is not called when added to the queue using ShellStreamer.startStream(StreamListener).
        Specified by:
        onStreamStart in interface ShellStreamer.StreamListener
        Parameters:
        shell - The ShellStreamer instance that handles this stream
